<article>
   <div style="width: 100%;"> 
      <h1 class="section-header">Who is Invited?</h1>
   </div>

   <p class="section-content">
      The invitation you/your family has received in the mail will state who is invited and how<br />
      many people are reserved under your name, including any plus ones. Only one person<br />
      mentioned on your invitation will be able to RSVP. Please review the “How to RSVP”<br />
      section for more details.<br /><br />

      In regards to children, unless stated in your invitation, we respectfully request no children<br />
      under the age of 16 at the reception.<br /><br />
   </p>

   <div style="width: 100%;"> 
      <h1 class="section-header">How to RSVP</h1>
   </div>

   <p class="section-content">
      Click the RSVP tab at the top of this page. Please write the full names of everyone you<br />
      are bringing to the wedding in accordance with the number of reserved spots stated in<br />
      your invitation. Please provide an email for contact purposes and any song requests you<br />
      may like to hear during the reception. Finally, provide us with any additional information<br />
      we should know (dietary restrictions, etc). If you run into any technical issues or have any<br />
      concerns, feel free to get in contact with us using the contact information at the bottom<br />
      of the page. All RSVPs must be sent through our website in order to secure your spot.<br /><br />
   </p>

   <div style="width: 100%;"> 
      <h1 class="section-header">Gift Registry</h1>
   </div>

   <p class="section-content">
      Our gift registry list is accessible through our website on the “Gift Registry” tab. Once<br />
      there, you’ll be able to click the link and access our registry via MyRegistry. You have the<br />
      option to mail the gift or bring it to the reception on our wedding day. If you wish to<br />
      purchase gifts from local stores in your area, you are more than welcome to find<br />
      alternatives for the items on our list, just be sure to return back to the website and check<br />
      off the items you have purchased. Please be sure to only check off an item as purchased<br />
      after you’ve purchased it. Since some items may fluctuate on their original websites, the<br />
      prices of items on our registry are subject to change.<br /><br />
   </p>

   <div style="width: 100%;"> 
      <h1 class="section-header">Photography</h1>
   </div>

   <p class="section-content">
      As we have hired a professional photographer for our wedding day, we kindly ask that<br />
      our ceremony remain unplugged. Please turn off all devices and enjoy being fully<br />
      present in the moment. However, after the ceremony and during the reception, guests<br />
      are more than welcome to take their own pictures. All we ask is to please forward any<br />
      pictures to the bride and groom afterwards.<br /><br />
   </p>

   <div style="width: 100%;"> 
      <h1 class="section-header">Seating</h1>
   </div>

   <p class="section-content">
      You are welcome to sit where you like for the ceremony. The only exception is that we<br />
      ask that the first row be reserved for members of the wedding party (parents,<br />
      grandparents, etc). For the reception, we are carefully arranging the tables so that our<br />
      guests are sitting with people they feel comfortable with. Please refer to the seating<br />
      chart upon entering the reception before seating.<br /><br />
   </p>

